sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Application
    participant JDBC as JDBC Driver
    participant PG as PostgreSQL Server

    %% Regular Query
    App->>JDBC: Create Statement (default ResultSet)
    App->>JDBC: Execute query (e.g., SELECT ...)
    JDBC->>PG: Send SQL query
    PG->>JDBC: Return all result rows at once
    JDBC-->>App: Provide ResultSet (forward-only)
    App->>JDBC: Iterate ResultSet (next())
    JDBC-->>App: Return row data
    App->>JDBC: Close ResultSet/Statement
    JDBC->>PG: Connection cleanup

    %% Scrollable ResultSet (Cursor)
    App->>JDBC: Create Statement (ResultSet.TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE or TYPE_SCROLL_SENSITIVE)
    App->>JDBC: Execute query (e.g., SELECT ...)
    JDBC->>PG: Send SQL query with cursor declaration
    PG->>JDBC: Open cursor, return initial rows
    JDBC-->>App: Provide scrollable ResultSet
    App->>JDBC: Move cursor (next(), previous(), absolute(), relative())
    JDBC->>PG: Fetch rows as needed (cursor stays open)
    PG->>JDBC: Return requested rows
    JDBC-->>App: Return row data
    App->>JDBC: Close ResultSet/Statement
    JDBC->>PG: Close cursor, cleanup connection
